The judge also granted Trump permission to file for dismissal of the case, setting deadlines for December.

Delays between two to four hours will guarantee snacks and beverages, while those exceeding four hours will include meals. This initiative aims to enhance passenger comfort during prolonged waits.

This action follows Ukraine's use of Western-supplied long-range missiles against Russian targets.

The court also appointed commissioners to inspect these points and will review the necessity of the restrictions next week.

description: During the first day of the Border Gavaskar Trophy Test in Perth, Nathan Lyon playfully asked Rishabh Pant about the upcoming IPL auction. description: Pancreatic cancer, a highly aggressive disease, often diagnosed late, has a low survival rate.  Genetic testing provides insights into individual risk and personalized treatment approaches.  Mutations in genes like KRAS, BRCA1, and BRCA2 are significant, and targeted therapies are being developed.  Germline mutations can identify individuals at risk, leading to enhanced surveillance and preventive measures.

description: India's batting lineup struggled in their first innings of the Perth Test against Australia, with the absence of Cheteshwar Pujara's anchoring presence keenly felt. description: Cambridge Dictionary has chosen "manifest" as its Word of the Year for 2024, reflecting the term's surge in popularity, driven by social media and celebrity endorsements. description: Aaryavir Sehwag, son of former Indian cricketer Virender Sehwag, impressed with a powerful batting performance. The inclusion of Washington Sundar highlights India's adaptive strategy, prioritizing a pace-heavy attack to exploit the pitch's characteristics.
title: When was the last time both R Ashwin, Jadeja missed Test for India?

description: Virat Kohli's struggles continued in the Perth Test against Australia on Friday as he was dismissed for just five runs in the first innings after India's stand-in captain Jasprit Bumrah opted to bat first at the Optus Stadium. Kohli's recent form has been a cause for concern, averagint just 22.72 in six Tests this year before entering the Border Gavaskar Trophy.
title: Virat Kohli's change in guard didn't work in Perth, out for 5

description: Russia has launched a new hypersonic missile, the Oreshnik, striking a Ukrainian facility in Dnipro. Putin claims the missile renders Western air defense systems useless. He justifies the attack as retaliation for Ukrainian strikes on Russian soil using Western-supplied missiles. The attack involved multiple warheads, marking an escalation in both weaponry and tactics.
title: Watch: Not ICBM, Russia fired missile that travels at '10 times the speed of sound'

description: BJP President JP Nadda responded to Congress Chief Mallikarjun Kharge's letter to the President regarding the Manipur violence. Nadda accused the Congress of sensationalizing the situation and blamed their past governance for the current unrest. He assured that the government is actively working to restore peace and normalcy in the state.
title: 'Attempts to sensationalise': Nadda slams Kharge's letter to prez on Manipur

description: Canada clarified that it possesses no evidence connecting Prime Minister Narendra Modi, External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar, or NSA Ajit Doval to criminal activities within the country. This follows accusations by Canadian PM Justin Trudeau, who alleged Indian government agents were involved in covert operations and serious crimes in Canada, claims India vehemently denied.
title: No evidence linking PM Modi, Jaishankar, NSA Doval to criminal activity: Canada

description: Hollywood star Richard Gere is moving his family to Spain.  The actor, known for films like 'Pretty Woman,' shared on 'The Tonight Show' that he and his Spanish wife, Alejandra Silva, plan to spend several years in Madrid. Gere emphasized that his children will thrive in a bilingual environment and assured fans that he will return to the U.S. eventually.
title: Richard Gere announces plans to leave America and move to Spain with family

description: India have handed Test debuts to fast bowler Harshit Rana and seam-up allrounder Nitish Kumar Reddy for the opening Border Gavaskar Trophy match against Australia at the Optus Stadium in Perth. India's stand-in captain Jasprit Bumrah won the toss and opted to bat first. The five-match series is also crucial to the teams' chances of qualifying for the World Test Championship final.
title: India vs Australia: Harshit, Nitish make Test debut in Perth

description: The International Criminal Court (ICC) has issued arrest warrants for Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and former Defence Minister Yoav Gallant. They are accused of war crimes and crimes against humanity during the 2023 Gaza conflict, including using starvation as a method of warfare and intentionally targeting civilians. Both deny the accusations.
title: Netanyahu ICC arrest warrant: What are the charges, where can he be arrested?

description: Indian all-rounder Washington Sundar has been chosen as the sole spinner for the first Test against Australia.  Captain Jasprit Bumrah confirmed the decision, citing Sundar's impressive track record in Australia and his recent form against New Zealand. Sundar's off-spin is expected to be particularly effective against Australia's left-handed dominant batting lineup, which includes Usman Khawaja and Travis Head.
title: Explained: Why Sundar found a place in India XI as sole spinner

description: The Indian Consulate in Canada has cancelled multiple consular camps due to security concerns, leaving thousands of elderly Indian and Canadian citizens without access to essential services. The cancellations follow a violent disruption at a previous camp and warnings from local authorities about their inability to guarantee safety.
title: Indian embassy cancels more consular camps in Canada over security concerns

description: Indian chess prodigy D Gukesh is set to challenge reigning champion Ding Liren for the World Championship title. The 14-game match begins in Singapore on Monday. Gukesh, currently ranked world No. 5, enters the match as the favorite against Ding, ranked No. 23. Gukesh's recent form and aggressive playing style are expected to test Ding.
title: World Chess C'ship: Can experienced Ding surprise Gukesh?

description: Moksha Group has acquired the assets of struggling B2B electronics startup Arzooo, which faced financial challenges due to aggressive expansion and heavy discounts. Moksha plans to utilize Arzooo's technology and network to empower small retailers with digital tools and financing options.
title: Consumer electronics company Arzooo goes for distress sale: What went wrong

description: Zepto, India's fastest-growing quick-commerce startup, has secured $350 million from domestic investors. CEO Aadit Palicha aims to transition Zepto into a majority Indian-owned company and list it on Indian stock exchanges. Palicha emphasized Zepto's commitment to fair pricing, denying allegations of predatory pricing and highlighting the company's role as a complementary service to traditional Kirana stores.
title: Zepto is not an 'Amazon or Walmart' but an Indian co with ...: CEO Aadit Palicha

description: A 74-year-old man, Anil Katyal, has been impersonating an IPS officer in Ghaziabad, using his elaborate ruse to influence police cases and network with officials. Katyal, who has an extensive corporate background, even attempted to leverage his fake identity to secure the release of an Indian billionaire held in Dubai.
title: After 35-yr career at big corporates, ex-honcho leads life as retired cop

description: Two Delhi police head constables, Seema Devi and Suman Hooda, achieved a remarkable feat by locating 104 missing children in just nine months. They traveled across states, overcoming language barriers and challenging terrains to reunite the children, aged 4 to 17, with their families. Their efforts involved meticulous investigation, utilizing technology, and building trust with locals.
title: Two cops reunite 104 missing kids with their families in 9 months

description: Jasprit Bumrah and Pat Cummins are defying stereotypes as Test captains of India and Australia, proving that fast bowlers can be successful leaders. Both embrace the challenges of captaincy, with Cummins already having significant experience in the role. They believe bowlers bring a unique perspective to leadership, emphasizing their tactical thinking and data-driven approach.
title: Bumrah, Cummins on pacer-captains: 'Hopefully it'll start a trend'

description: Pam Bondi has been named as US Attorney General by Donald Trump, succeeding Matt Gaetz, who withdrew amid a federal investigation. Bondi, a staunch Trump ally, previously defended him in his first impeachment trial and supported him during his recent hush money trial. Trump praised Bondi's commitment and outlined his vision for the Department of Justice to prioritise crime fighting and national security.
title: Trump taps loyalist Pam Bondi for US attorney general after Matt Gaetz withdraws

description: The actress says that both, her beau businessman Ashish Kanakia and she were looking for a long-term, stable relationship.
title: Exclusive: Shazahn Padamsee gets engaged, to tie the knot next year

description: Delhi-NCR's air quality, though seeing slight improvement, is predicted to remain 'very poor' due to meteorological factors like lack of rain and fog exacerbating pollution.
